irvice\ncosts no\nheating.\nsoon/\nER COMPANY\nTo Hold Boy Scout\nFirst Aid Meeting\nAt Pandora-Gilboa\nBoy Scouts and Explorers'of the\nPutnam district will compete in a\nfirst aid meet at the Pandora-Gilboa\nhigh school gymnasium Saturday at\n7:30 p. m., Stanley Goodwin, chair\nman of the district camping and\nactivities committee has announced.\nAmong committee members plan\nning the event are Ralph Reichen\nbach, Robert Sawyer and Clayton\nHarkness, all of Bluffton.\nBetween 75 and 100 Scouts are ex\npected to participate. First Aid\nproblems will be presented to each\ngroup and the members will then\napply proper aid techniques. Patrols\nand crews will be rated according to\ncorrect analysis of injuries, proper\nadministration of first aid and neat\nness.\nRichland Center\nMrs. Cora Balmer returned home\nlast Tuesday after spending about\nfour months in San Diego, California,\nwith Mr. and Mrs. Mert Farmer.\nMr. and Mrs. Paul Amstutz and\nfamily, Mr. and Mrs. Herman Hilty\nand family and Mr. and Mrs. Delbert\nHall and daughter were Saturday\nsupper guests of Mr. and Mrs. Philip\nHilty and daughter Minerva.\nMr. and Mrs. Elwood Brauen of\nGahanna spent the week end with Mr.\nand Mrs. Otis Fett and Mrs. Emma\nRoof. Mr. and Mrs. James Palte\nwere Easter Sunday guests.\nMr. and Mrs. Jesse Augsburger\nand Mr. and Mrs. Robert Hadsell and\nfamily were Easter Sunday dinner\nguests of Mr. and Mrs. Darrell Augs\nburger and family of Lima.\nMr. and Mrs. Don Hughes of Ga\nhanna were week-end guests of Mr.\nand Mrs. Raymond Matter. Other\nSunday dinner guests were Mr. and\nMrs. W. H. Cool of Springfield and\nMr. and Mrs. Jim Matter.\nMr. Cal Schaublin was a Friday\nsupper guest of Mrs. Walter Schau\nblin.\nMrs. Richard Smith and sons spent\nWednesday afternoon with Mrs. Rich\nard Oglesbee and children.\nMr. and Mrs. Pearle Eikenbary of\nAkron were week-end guests of Mr.\nand Mrs. Guy Eikenbary. Other Eas\nter Sunday dinner guests were Mr.\nand Mrs. John Nonnamaker and\nsons, Mr. and Mrs. Jim Nonnamaker\nand son, and Judy and Tom Chidest\ner.\nMr. and Mrs. John Barnhart were\nSunday dinner guests of Mr. and\nMrs. Don Dillman and family. After\nnoon callers were Mr. and Mrs. Em\nI ory Basinger and daughter Elaine.\nMrs. William Amstutz and Mrs.\nJames Kolvas and children spent\nThursday afternoon with Mr. and\nI Mrs. Floyd Smith of Findlay.\nMr. and Mrs. Clyde Grant and son\nwere Sunday supper guests of Mrs.\nJ. I. Luginbuhl Mr. Cal Schaublin\nwas a Friday caller.\nMr. and Mrs. Hilarv Bunger and\nsons of Battle Creek, Michigan, were\nweek-end guests of Mr. and Mrs.\nHarold Hendricks.\nMr. and Mrs. Charles Sharp of Nor\nwalk, Mrs. Ella Dillman, Mr. and\nMrs. Robert Marquart and daughter\nand Miss Cassie Luginbuhl were.\nSunday dinner guests of Mrs. Amos\nand Mr. and Mrs. Weldon Luginbuhl.\nMr. and Mrs. Donivan Moser and\nfamily of Milford were Monday cal\nlers.\nMr. and Mrs. Robert Gerber, son\nDavid and daughter Karen were Sun\nday dinner guests of Mrs. Amos Ger\nber and Mr. and Mrs. Marion Hoch\nstettler and daughter. Mrs. Sam Koh\nler was a Thursday afternoon caller.\nMr. and Mrs. Francis Marquart\nand daughter of Mt. Vernon spent\nSaturday night and Sunday with Mr.\nand Mrs. Ed Marquart. Mr. and Mrs.\nFaye Isham of Lima were Sunday\ndinner guests. Past week callers were\nMr. and Mrs. Melvin Marquart and\ndaughter and Mr. and Mrs. Richard\nCore.\nMr. and Mrs. Nolan Benroth and\nfamily. Mr. Roland Conner and Mr.\nJim Baber were Sunday supper\nguests of Mr. and Mrs. Joe Follas\nand daughter Joar. and Mr. Sam Bas\ninger.\nElmer and Dan Smith spent Satur\nday at the Richard Smith home.\nMr. and Mrs. Dale Risser and son\nwere Easter dinner guests of Mr. and\nMrs. Wilbur Risser and daughter.\nMr. and Mrs. Burke Moser and son\nspent the week end at Hamilton with\nher parents.\nMr. and Mrs. Robert Matter and\nson Vernie were Sunday guests of her\nparents, Mr. and Mrs. Dewitt Knight\nand daughter of Findlay.\nMrs. Henry Green and son Bob\nreturned home last Monday evening\nafter spending a week with Lt. and\nMrs. James Green at Savanna, Ga.\nMr. and Mrs. Emanuel Boutwell\nand daughters, Mr. and Mrs. Russell\nSchaublin and family, Mr. and Mrs.\nWilford Qratz and daughter, and Mr.\nand Mrs. Gene Johnson and daugh\nter spent Easter with their mother\nand grandmother, Mrs. Walter Schau\nblin. Evening callers were Mr. and\nMrs. John Tnomas and family.\nMr. and Mrs. Richard Smith and\nsons were Sunday supper guests of\nher parents, Mr. and Mrs. Odes Sher\ner.\nMr. and Mrs. Robert Reichenbach\nand family, Mr. and Mrs. Robert\nMayer and daughter and Mr. and\nMrs. William Reichenbach were\nEaster dinner guests of Mrs. Bar\nbara Reichenbach and family.\nMr. and Mrs. Ronnie Cramer and\ndaughter of Rawson, Mr. and Mrs.\nRichard Daumelin of Findlay, Mr.\nand Mrs. Richard Kohler and family,\nMr. and Mrs. Charles Fridley of\nLima, Mr. and Mrs. Rhuel Kohler\nand Mr. and Mrs. Gene Kohler were\nEaster dinner guests of Mrs. Sam\nKohler and daughter.\nMr. and Mrs. Quinten Burkholder\nspent Saturday evening with Mr. and\nAirs. Donivan Montgomery and fam\nily-\nMr. and Mrs. Floyd Smith. Mr.\nJohn Amstutz, Mrs. Kathryn Griffith\nand Mr. James Kolvas spent Satur\nday evening at the William Amstutz\nhome. Mr. and Mrs. Richard Olt and\nson were Sunday supper guests. Mr.\nand Mrs. James Kolvas and children\nreturned to their home in South Bend,\nILUFFTOf NEWS, BLUFFTON\nTHE OHIO\nInd., after she and the children had\nspent the week at the Amstutz home.\nMrs. Cora Balmer spent Easter\nwith her mother and brother, Mrs.\nLydia Badertscher and Milton.\nMr. and Mrs. William Riechenbach\nspent Saturday evening with Mr. and\nMrs. Robert Mayer and daughter of\nLima.\nCome See\nANN PAGE\nGolden Corn\nFluffo\nCrisco\nMrs. Walter Schaublin attended a\ndinner Saturday evening in McComb\nin honor of the golden wedding an\nniversary of Mr. and Mrs. Henry\nHilty and the 19th wedding annivers\nary of Mr. and Mrs. Harold Young.\nOthers present wer